President Joe Biden spoke at the South Court Auditorium, addressing the recent tragedy in Florida and the signing of a bill in memory of the Pulse nightclub shooting. He expressed his condolences to the families affected by the tragedy and assured them that the administration is providing all necessary assistance. Biden emphasized the importance of remembering the lives lost and preventing such incidents from happening again. He thanked the members of Congress for their commitment to enshrining the memory of the victims in law. The President also acknowledged the emotional toll that signing such a bill can have and expressed his gratitude to the survivors for their courage. He ended his speech by promising to continue working towards equity in all areas.